HEADWORD: Preremote
<hw>Pre`re*mote</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>More remote in
previous time or prior order.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In some cases two more links of causation may be introduced; one
of them may be termed the <qex>preremote</qex> cause, the other the
postremote effect.</q> <rj><qau>E. Darwin.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Prerequire</ent>⟦br⟧
